The country is recording good progress in the ongoing mop-up of pupils to join secondary schools as part of the government&rsquo;s 100% transition policy. According to education cs prof George Magoha, three counties Bomet, Nyamira and Mandera have already registered the 100% transition signalling the success of the mop-up exercise. And as Daniel Kariuki reports, the ongoing mop-up exercise had already seen an increase of 10.3% in the number of candidates registering for the 2021 national examinations.